Fit a mixed meta-analysis regression model of trends

anlz_mixmeta.Rd

Fit a mixed meta-analysis regression model of trends

anlz_mixmeta(avgseason, yrstr = 2000, yrend = 2017)

Arguments

avgseason

output from anlz_avgseason
yrstr

numeric for starting year
yrend

numeric for ending year

Value

A list of mixmeta fitted model objects

Examples

library(dplyr)

# fit models with function
tomod <- rawdat %>%
  filter(station %in% 32) %>%
  filter(param %in% 'chl')
trans <- 'boxcox'
mods <- list(
  gam0 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam0', trans = trans),
  gam1 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam1', trans = trans),
  gam2 = anlz_gam(tomod, mod = 'gam2', trans = trans)
  )
avgseason <- anlz_avgseason(mods = mods, doystr = 90, doyend = 180)
anlz_mixmeta(avgseason, yrstr = 2000, yrend = 2017)
